# TradeGuard Web (Next.js)

See also `apps/web/AGENTS.md` for Next.js version-specific notes.

## API client

- `apps/web/src/lib/api.ts` — all backend calls via `fetchJson`.
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` set → browser calls Railway directly (cross-origin, needs CORS).
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` unset → same-origin `/api/*` proxied by `next.config.ts` rewrites.

Prefer same-origin rewrites in dev to avoid CORS masking server errors.

## Key routes

- `/approvals` — manual trade approval queue
- `/onboarding` — Robinhood OAuth connect wizard
- `/journal` — trade log
- `/strategies` — semi-auto rules

## Auth

- Clerk optional; when disabled, demo user via `X-Demo-User-Email` cookie.
- `setAuthTokenGetter` in `api.ts` wires Clerk JWT when configured.

## UI patterns

- Risk verdicts render from structured API responses — do not parse LLM markdown for metrics.
- Show clear BLOCK / CAUTION / ALLOW states matching backend enums.
